GAINS detection system(Gamma Array for Inelastic
Neutron Scattering) consists of eight HPGe detectors
(100% relative efficiency), placed at 110 and 150 deg
with respect to the neutron beam. Distance between the
center of the sample and the front side of each
detector is of the order of 15 cm. Read-out by four
DC440 Acquiris digitizers. Typical energy resolution of
the large HPGe detectors read-out by the digitized
acquisition if of the order of 2.5 keV (FWHM) and the
time resolution is of the order of 8 ns.
